[commands]
check_dig=$USER1$/check_dig -H $HOSTADDRESS$ -l $ARG1$
[name]
check_dig

[info]
Checks DNS Servers on a specific host using dig.

[why]
To verify the functionality of the DNS server.

[how]
By using the dig command to resolve a hostname. The plugin lets you specify a hostname and the expected ipaddress.

[platforms]
Not platform dependent.


[categories]
DNS

[support]
4

[tags]
dns, domain name, hostname, resolve
